President Obama emphasizes the importance of creating a workplace that is supportive of working families in an op-ed published on the Huffington Post. He discusses the need for policies such as flexibility, paid family leave, affordable childcare, and a decent minimum wage. These policies are not luxuries but basic needs for working parents. Obama highlights the positive impact of family-friendly policies on businesses and the economy, as well as the need for action at the federal level. He announces his intention to sign a Presidential Memorandum expanding access to flexible work schedules, calls on Congress to pass the Pregnant Workers Fairness Act, and directs his Secretary of Labor to invest in job-training programs that provide childcare. Obama expresses his personal connection to the issue as a son, husband, and father, and reaffirms his commitment to fighting for a fair and inclusive America.